.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-trim 1  "rom-weaver-trim "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-trim \- Trim or restore supported ROM and disc\-image formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver trim\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-e\fR|\fB\-\-extension\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-in\-place\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-simulate\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-revert\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-recursive\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-rom\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR] [\fB\-\-revert\-marker\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISOURCE\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Trim or restore supported ROM and disc\-image formats
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Destination file for trimmed output (single trim\-eligible source only)
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-extension\fR \fI<EXTENSION>\fR
Output extension for side\-by\-side output (supports `{ext}` placeholder, for example `trim.{ext}`)
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-in\-place\fR
Trim the source file in place instead of writing a new file
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-simulate\fR
Simulate trim operations without writing output files
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-revert\fR
Restore trimmed files using an embedded revert marker when present; otherwise use the format\*(Aqs header\-derived size (NDS/3DS) or next power of two (GBA). Not supported for xiso or rvz\-scrub
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-recursive\fR
Do not recursively scan subdirectories when input sources include folders
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-rom\-filter\fR
Disable the default ROM\-only filter applied to archive payloads before trimming
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR
Disable archive auto\-extract; only trim direct file inputs
.TP
\fB\-\-revert\-marker\fR
Embed a small footer in the trimmed output so it can later be reverted to a byte\-identical original
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fISOURCE\fR>
File, container, or directory to trim (repeatable)
